1
00:00:20,037 --> 00:00:23,040
We will march from Hongsawadi this day, never to return.

2
00:00:23,410 --> 00:00:24,411
You should get going.

3
00:00:24,503 --> 00:00:27,800
Mingyi Swa, go after Nares and bring his people back.

4
00:00:27,803 --> 00:00:31,200
- To do so, is nothing less than an act of rebellion against Hongsawadi.
- I only wanted to D444go home.

5
00:00:31,503 --> 00:00:34,000
A place to sleep in peace, without the constant fear of death.

6
00:00:34,250 --> 00:00:36,920
Mingyi Naung struck Prince Nares unconscious

7
00:00:37,277 --> 00:00:38,000
How dare you!

8
00:00:38,077 --> 00:00:40,257
Is this how you raise your son?

9
00:00:40,263 --> 00:00:42,840
To eliminate an enemy,

10
00:00:42,970 --> 00:00:44,200
I will do whatever it takes.

11
00:00:44,403 --> 00:00:46,320
I beg your permission

12
00:00:46,404 --> 00:00:49,200
to let Nares return to Phitsanulok.

13
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:51,000
This campaign against Lan Xang,

14
00:00:51,143 --> 00:00:52,560
it does have its advantages, I suppose.

15
00:00:52,977 --> 00:00:54,840
At last, I shall see Naresuan’s face once more.

16
00:00:55,837 --> 00:00:58,720
The plague has struck. Everyone is dead.

17
00:00:59,623 --> 00:01:01,360
Is it smallpox that has stricken Prince Nares?

18
00:01:01,660 --> 00:01:03,080
Wait for the news, Brother.

19
00:01:03,283 --> 00:01:05,480
Then, you may perform the merit-making

20
00:01:05,837 --> 00:01:08,840
for your sworn brother later.

21
00:01:10,143 --> 00:01:14,400
Everyone believes, without a doubt, that I am going to die.

22
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:39,760
After being at death's door with the smallpox,

23
00:01:40,643 --> 00:01:42,480
I spent a full year recovering.

24
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:49,560
Hongsawadi believes that I have grown weak,

25
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:52,160
and thus, they have ceased to fear me.

26
00:01:55,361 --> 00:01:57,200
A message from Prince Mingyi Swa, Your Highness.

27
00:02:10,937 --> 00:02:12,550
Yet the bond of brotherhood

28
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:15,120
between Mingyi Swa and I

29
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,500
has never faded.

30
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,241
Brother.

31
00:02:58,417 --> 00:02:59,800
Are you fully recovered?

32
00:03:00,710 --> 00:03:02,840
It is by the grace of fortune that I escaped death.

33
00:03:07,377 --> 00:03:09,280
- Brother.
- My brother.

34
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:16,680
My horse was injured upon the road, hence my delay.

35
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:20,400
I can wait. I knew that, regardless of the path, you would come for me.

36
00:03:24,601 --> 00:03:26,320
On every Winter Solstice,

37
00:03:27,770 --> 00:03:29,480
we vowed to meet here.

38
00:03:30,481 --> 00:03:31,600
It is fortunate that I have arrived in time.

39
00:03:43,997 --> 00:03:44,998
The Winter Solstice

40
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:47,600
is when the sun possesses its greatest strength.

41
00:03:49,803 --> 00:03:53,040
They say that prayers made to the sun on this day

42
00:03:53,383 --> 00:03:55,720
hold the power to turn the tides of fate.

43
00:03:56,880 --> 00:03:59,640
Then, let us offer our prayers together.

44
00:04:05,323 --> 00:04:08,400
- I pray that our two lands...
- I pray that our two lands…

45
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,880
- May dwell together in enduring peace.
- May dwell together in enduring peace.

46
00:04:13,557 --> 00:04:15,560
- Bound as brothers, kin of the same soul.
- Bound as brothers, kin of the same soul.

47
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:18,201
- For all eternity.
- For all eternity.

48
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:37,341
[Hongsawadi, 2122 B.E.]

49
00:05:37,351 --> 00:05:38,360
[3 years later]

50
00:05:38,390 --> 00:05:40,320
The reason I have summoned you all today

51
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,400
is for a matter of great urgency.

52
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:47,240
The King of Lan Xang has sent word that

53
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:50,440
his ministers and officials are in open rebellion.

54
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:54,560
Therefore, he requests that Hongsawadi

55
00:05:54,950 --> 00:05:56,720
dispatch an army to suppress them.

56
00:06:01,377 --> 00:06:02,378
By your leave,

57
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:05,361
as Your Majesty is currently indisposed by illness,

58
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:10,000
I volunteer to lead the army and suppress these rebels myself, Your Majesty.

59
00:06:15,910 --> 00:06:17,120
I have learned that

60
00:06:19,163 --> 00:06:20,320
the cause of this unrest

61
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:22,840
lies with the King of Lan Xang,

62
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:25,280
for he has neglected the Ten Royal Virtues

63
00:06:26,650 --> 00:06:28,520
and bestowed rank upon his own kin.

64
00:06:30,003 --> 00:06:34,040
This has sown discontent among the officials, causing them to flee into hiding

65
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,760
and unite in rebellion.

66
00:06:40,717 --> 00:06:41,718
In this campaign,

67
00:06:43,257 --> 00:06:45,200
I must handle the matter myself.

68
00:06:46,463 --> 00:06:50,440
Go and prepare the armies to be ready.

69
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:01,080
Father!

70
00:07:01,697 --> 00:07:04,480
Soldier! Summon the Royal Physician at once!

71
00:07:04,930 --> 00:07:05,931
Hurry!

72
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:25,041
[Mingyi Naung, the youngest son of Jaisingh]

73
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:29,241
Mingyi Naung.

74
00:07:30,157 --> 00:07:31,177
What is the matter, Brother?

75
00:07:31,840 --> 00:07:32,960
Cease your eating at once.

76
00:07:33,417 --> 00:07:34,837
The sight of it truly vexes my eyes.

77
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,840
If it vexes you, then turn your eyes elsewhere.

78
00:07:43,783 --> 00:07:44,784
Hey!

79
00:07:46,230 --> 00:07:47,231
Mingyi Naung.

80
00:07:47,297 --> 00:07:48,298
Enough!

81
00:07:53,603 --> 00:07:54,921
Do not quarrel.

82
00:08:01,957 --> 00:08:02,958
Father.

83
00:08:09,290 --> 00:08:12,480
How is Grandfather's condition, Your Highness?

84
00:08:14,370 --> 00:08:15,640
His Majesty's condition is not good.

85
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,961
The Royal Physician has forbidden him from traveling.

86
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:24,481
I must go to suppress the rebellion in Lan Xang in his stead.

87
00:08:25,881 --> 00:08:28,282
You both stay here and take good care of your Grandfather.

88
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:31,683
If anything should happen,

89
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:34,040
send word to me immediately.

90
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:37,641
Yes, Father.

91
00:08:38,760 --> 00:08:39,840
And most importantly,

92
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:43,161
the news of your Grandfather's illness

93
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:46,760
must not be leaked under any circumstances.

94
00:08:50,463 --> 00:08:51,464
Yes, Father.

95
00:08:54,550 --> 00:08:58,280
King Bayinnaung is over 60 years of age.

96
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:02,280
This illness is no small matter.

97
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:04,920
It is a sign that

98
00:09:05,697 --> 00:09:09,640
Hongsawadi may soon face a change of reign.

99
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:14,600
Even though Crown Prince Jaisingh has been appointed

100
00:09:14,621 --> 00:09:17,080
as the successor to the throne,

101
00:09:18,370 --> 00:09:21,760
once the merit and power of King Bayinnaung are gone,

102
00:09:22,663 --> 00:09:25,920
there may be those who seek to seize the throne for themselves.

103
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:34,601
[City of Inwa]

104
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:49,841
[King Thado Minsaw of Inwa]

105
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:00,917
Princess Natshin Medaw has arrived.

106
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:17,121
[Princess Natshin Medaw]

107
00:10:17,140 --> 00:10:19,141
[Daughter of King Thado Minsaw]

108
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:37,560
Father, you have summoned me. What is the reason?

109
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:39,800
King Bayinnaung,

110
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:43,240
your Royal Uncle, has fallen ill.

111
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:48,361
It is only fitting that we pay him a visit.

112
00:10:57,550 --> 00:11:00,717
The rebel nobles have now been completely suppressed.

113
00:11:01,170 --> 00:11:03,560
The King of Lan Xang, in gratitude for your mercy,

114
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:07,080
has offered a pair of tusker elephants, gold ornaments,

115
00:11:07,277 --> 00:11:09,560
and precious gems as tribute, Your Majesty.

116
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:14,120
All these tributes,

117
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:19,217
I bestow upon the Crown Prince as a reward for your victory.

118
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:21,520
Furthermore, I express my gratitude

119
00:11:21,737 --> 00:11:24,720
for a mission successfully accomplished.

120
00:11:25,477 --> 00:11:26,880
It is your Grace, Your Majesty.

121
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:33,400
I beg your royal pardon, Your Majesty.

122
00:11:33,803 --> 00:11:36,920
Binnya Dala, what business do you have?

123
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:38,823
King Thado Minsaw

124
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:42,520
has arrived with Princess Natshin Medaw, his daughter.

125
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:44,840
They request an audience with you, Your Majesty.

126
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:48,160
Their arrival is sudden, with no prior notice.

127
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:49,640
This bodes ill.

128
00:11:50,890 --> 00:11:53,840
Not only that, King Thado Minsaw

129
00:11:54,123 --> 00:11:55,683
has also brought ten thousand troops with him.

130
00:11:56,033 --> 00:11:59,960
At this moment, they have halted outside the city walls, Your Majesty.

131
00:12:17,322 --> 00:12:18,720
I prostrate before you, Your Majesty.

132
00:12:20,430 --> 00:12:24,480
Welcome the King of Inwa and the Princess to be seated as is fitting.

133
00:12:42,610 --> 00:12:44,100
That you have come to seek us this time

134
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,920
without prior notice. What is the reason?

135
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:52,920
I come to seek an audience with King Bayinnaung, my elder brother,

136
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:56,921
out of the deep respect I hold for Your Majesty,

137
00:12:57,517 --> 00:12:59,640
and purely as a kinsman, Your Majesty.

138
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:01,800
Movement of troops

139
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:06,000
requires a royal decree from the King of Hongsawadi.

140
00:13:06,910 --> 00:13:08,480
This, you know well.

141
00:13:09,300 --> 00:13:13,320
Yet you bring tens of thousands to our very walls.

142
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:17,400
Are you quite certain this is merely a visit among kin?

143
00:13:18,441 --> 00:13:21,080
You are being far too suspicious, Your Highness.

144
00:13:24,930 --> 00:13:27,880
I wished only to pay homage at the Shwemawdaw Pagoda,

145
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:30,360
but as a woman,

146
00:13:31,160 --> 00:13:33,661
I feared the dangers of the road.

147
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:37,801
I brought these guards only for my own peace of mind.

148
00:13:39,330 --> 00:13:41,360
If this has offended you,

149
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:44,600
I humbly beg Your Majesty’s forgiveness.

150
00:13:47,937 --> 00:13:48,938
Never mind.

151
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,121
It is just as well that you have come.

152
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:54,281
At this time, there are foul rumors afoot.

153
00:13:55,170 --> 00:13:59,000
People whisper that I am gravely ill.

154
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:02,210
Now that you have seen me with your own eyes,

155
00:14:03,070 --> 00:14:04,710
should you hear those rumors again,

156
00:14:05,850 --> 00:14:08,400
you will not be misled into thinking I am near death.

157
00:14:23,943 --> 00:14:25,720
The King of Inwa surely comes with ill intent.

158
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:28,360
He must have heard that you, Father, have fallen ill.

159
00:14:28,910 --> 00:14:30,680
That is why he brought his army to scout our strength.

160
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:33,481
If we let this pass, it will become a grave danger, Your Majesty.

161
00:14:34,497 --> 00:14:38,360
Thado Minsaw may be of a different mother,

162
00:14:39,030 --> 00:14:40,320
but I share the same father.

163
00:14:41,237 --> 00:14:42,897
I consider him a younger brother,

164
00:14:43,930 --> 00:14:46,280
and he is also wedded to your elder sister.

165
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:49,760
Thus, he is doubly bound to you as kin.

166
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:52,400
Whatever you intend to do,

167
00:14:53,610 --> 00:14:55,480
you must consider it with the utmost care.

168
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:57,360
But I do not trust Inwa.

169
00:15:05,890 --> 00:15:07,360
Though Thado Minsaw

170
00:15:09,137 --> 00:15:10,960
may be ambitious,

171
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:14,300
he still holds a great deal of respect for me.

172
00:15:15,223 --> 00:15:16,920
He would not dare to act against me.

173
00:15:18,163 --> 00:15:20,520
You need not worry yourself before the trouble arises.

174
00:15:22,003 --> 00:15:24,040
I am not dead yet.

175
00:15:26,083 --> 00:15:28,084
Please, take your medicine first, Your Majesty.

176
00:15:33,783 --> 00:15:36,440
He uses his own child as a shield.

177
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:39,441
What is to stop me from doing the same?

178
00:15:43,290 --> 00:15:46,120
I will not wed Princess Natshin Medaw.

179
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:48,721
I have no affection for her.

180
00:15:49,297 --> 00:15:50,360
You do not have to like her.

181
00:15:51,523 --> 00:15:54,880
But you must enter the wedding ceremony and take her as your consort.

182
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:57,880
Whether you love or loathe her is entirely up to you.

183
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:05,801
In the future, you may take as many concubines as you wish.

184
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:09,240
But today, you must go through with this ceremony for me.

185
00:16:14,610 --> 00:16:17,520
You intend to use Natshin Medaw as a hostage

186
00:16:18,611 --> 00:16:20,160
to keep the King of Inwa under your control.

187
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,201
Yes.

188
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:27,000
Tomorrow, I shall negotiate with the King of Inwa.

189
00:16:27,490 --> 00:16:29,800
And I will inform your Grandfather of this matter.

190
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:33,480
You cannot defy this. It is an order!

191
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:49,650
Open the palace gates!

192
00:16:50,663 --> 00:16:51,960
Prince Mingyi Swa,

193
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:53,661
At such a late hour,

194
00:16:53,857 --> 00:16:56,120
unless there is an order to open them…

195
00:16:58,120 --> 00:16:59,520
Do you see this royal seal?

196
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:02,700
It is the seal of the Crown Prince Jaisingh.

197
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:11,720
Mangjaparo and I are departing on a secret mission.

198
00:17:13,297 --> 00:17:14,880
Do not let a word of this slip to anyone.

199
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:17,721
- Yes, Your Highness.
- Yes, Your Highness.

200
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:35,057
Let us return to Inwa.

201
00:17:35,776 --> 00:17:37,200
Mingyi Swa has already fled.

202
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:41,810
If we remain here, people will only mock and shame us.

203
00:17:41,862 --> 00:17:44,200
I myself never desired to wed Mingyi Swa.

204
00:17:45,377 --> 00:17:48,280
I only consented to repay my debt of gratitude to you, Father.

205
00:17:51,560 --> 00:17:54,440
He is a man in name only, yet he fled like a coward.

206
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:58,800
If I must bow my head and endure this shame alone,

207
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:02,040
I shall never be able to rest in peace.

208
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:11,440
What do you intend to do?

209
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:18,960
Mingyi Swa must be made to realize

210
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:22,240
what happens when he incurs my wrath,

211
00:18:24,760 --> 00:18:26,040
and what the consequences shall be.

212
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:30,781
[Chan Royal Palace, Phitsanulok]

213
00:18:35,640 --> 00:18:37,500
You fled the city and yet you still dare to lie.

214
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:39,401
How could you have become such a man?

215
00:18:39,841 --> 00:18:41,160
I truly never could have imagined it.

216
00:18:43,937 --> 00:18:45,150
I was merely wondering

217
00:18:46,323 --> 00:18:49,400
what you would have done in my place.

218
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:53,360
Are you suggesting that you are as wicked as I?

219
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:57,600
And as for stealing the royal seal and fleeing like this,

220
00:18:58,203 --> 00:19:00,204
do you have any idea what punishment awaits your return?

221
00:19:06,470 --> 00:19:07,471
Never mind.

222
00:19:10,157 --> 00:19:13,480
My other offenses are far more severe than this.

223
00:19:17,110 --> 00:19:20,440
So you fled this far, thinking that no one would dare follow you?

224
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:24,760
Even if they follow,

225
00:19:25,930 --> 00:19:28,240
as I am a guest within your city,

226
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:32,760
you are obligated to protect me from any harm.

227
00:19:33,360 --> 00:19:34,361
Is that not true?

228
00:19:37,320 --> 00:19:41,960
My brother grows more cunning by the day. You cannot be trusted at all.

229
00:19:45,280 --> 00:19:46,920
It is because I have had a fine teacher.

230
00:19:54,837 --> 00:19:57,120
It is because you put your own desires above all else.

231
00:19:57,617 --> 00:20:01,040
And now, look, Mingyi Swa has fled.

232
00:20:01,370 --> 00:20:03,400
Natshin Medaw must endure this humiliation,

233
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:08,320
while Thado Minsaw seethes with resentment for his daughter.

234
00:20:10,550 --> 00:20:13,120
I shall send men to drag Mingyi Swa back to face his crimes.

235
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:15,601
- For defying my orders.
- Jaisingh!

236
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:18,300
Do not merely issue commands.

237
00:20:19,863 --> 00:20:21,480
Or punish any who fail to obey.

238
00:20:23,230 --> 00:20:26,840
As a ruler, you cannot behave in such a manner.

239
00:20:28,563 --> 00:20:31,400
If one is not resolute, how then can one hope to rule the people, Your Majesty?

240
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:32,880
To rule by fear

241
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:35,760
cannot last long.

242
00:20:37,123 --> 00:20:40,000
When those who are oppressed are pushed beyond their endurance,

243
00:20:41,190 --> 00:20:42,920
they will no longer fear even death itself.

244
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:47,200
Those who do not fear death, how many could there truly be?

245
00:20:50,590 --> 00:20:52,120
Your Majesty has reached a great age.

246
00:20:53,320 --> 00:20:54,720
Your health and vigor are in decline.

247
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:57,500
Perhaps it has caused your heart to soften as well!

248
00:20:58,623 --> 00:21:02,640
It is because you see that I am old, is it not?

249
00:21:04,277 --> 00:21:09,000
That you dared to arrange a match for Mingyi Swa without consulting me.

250
00:21:09,680 --> 00:21:11,000
I told you

251
00:21:13,081 --> 00:21:16,482
that Thado Minsaw would never dare defy me.

252
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:18,000
But you would not listen!

253
00:21:21,070 --> 00:21:24,440
You feared you could not control the King of Inwa,

254
00:21:25,897 --> 00:21:27,560
so you sought to take his child as a hostage.

255
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:32,760
Do you think I shall drop dead tomorrow?

256
00:21:33,390 --> 00:21:34,391
Do you?

257
00:21:36,791 --> 00:21:41,590
By your leave, I have never harbored any ill intent.

258
00:21:44,760 --> 00:21:47,560
Father, you have been ill for many months.

259
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:50,480
Your strength is struggling to return.

260
00:21:51,617 --> 00:21:54,760
Certain matters of state simply require a firm hand, Your Majesty.

261
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:59,700
Decisive as you are, then?

262
00:22:00,721 --> 00:22:01,722
Is that so?

263
00:22:04,130 --> 00:22:05,131
Yes, Your Majesty.

264
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:12,801
Get out!

265
00:22:14,130 --> 00:22:15,131
Get out!

266
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:27,120
Song Kwae, a paradise between two rivers.

267
00:23:29,160 --> 00:23:32,200
It truly lives up to its name.

268
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:35,160
I was born here, and I was raised here.

269
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:39,040
In my eyes, no other place is as beautiful as Song Kwae.

270
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:58,000
Did you catch any fish, young man?

271
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:03,840
I haven't caught a single one, Uncle.

272
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:09,520
I caught quite a lot myself today.

273
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:12,200
Here, take some to share for your meal.

274
00:24:19,570 --> 00:24:21,480
You two shouldn't be so lazy.

275
00:24:22,520 --> 00:24:24,560
The river is teeming with fish right now.

276
00:24:26,040 --> 00:24:27,700
If you keep lounging around like this,

277
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:29,640
you'll end up starving to death.

278
00:24:31,997 --> 00:24:34,040
Yes, thank you, Uncle.

279
00:24:55,123 --> 00:24:56,720
You seem happy and at ease here.

280
00:24:57,743 --> 00:24:59,240
Unlike when you were in Hongsawadi.

281
00:25:01,363 --> 00:25:02,641
This is my home.

282
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:06,400
I go where I wish, and I do as I please.

283
00:25:12,041 --> 00:25:13,200
Is that what home is, then?

284
00:25:14,710 --> 00:25:15,711
Home

285
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:18,000
is a place that belongs to us.

286
00:25:19,823 --> 00:25:21,040
A place where we are masters of our own fate.

287
00:25:22,280 --> 00:25:26,081
Within our own home, no one can coerce or oppress us.

288
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:30,321
Phitsanulok is my home.

289
00:25:31,843 --> 00:25:33,200
Hongsawadi is not.

290
00:25:47,663 --> 00:25:51,520
If home is as you say,

291
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:56,640
Then Hongsawadi is not my home either.

292
00:26:06,360 --> 00:26:09,680
By your leave, I am Mangjaparo, Your Highness.

293
00:26:18,490 --> 00:26:21,200
King Bayinnaung of Hongsawadi has issued a royal command.

294
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:25,080
For you to attend an urgent audience at once, Your Highness.

295
00:26:39,730 --> 00:26:40,800
Why has Grandfather

296
00:26:42,120 --> 00:26:43,760
come to this remote, ruined temple?

297
00:26:47,680 --> 00:26:49,881
Why not allow me to return for an audience at Hongsawadi?

298
00:26:52,370 --> 00:26:53,882
That you wish to speak with His Majesty,

299
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:57,241
must surely be kept away from any prying eyes and ears.

300
00:27:18,197 --> 00:27:19,920
I have lived for over 60 years now.

301
00:27:21,597 --> 00:27:25,560
Long enough to see that the world is changing.

302
00:27:26,800 --> 00:27:30,160
In the days to come, trade and diplomacy

303
00:27:30,960 --> 00:27:32,600
shall be more vital than military might.

304
00:27:34,637 --> 00:27:37,200
We can no longer rule by the sword as we did before.

305
00:27:39,040 --> 00:27:41,000
If we mean to preserve this empire,

306
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:46,200
Hongsawadi must forge alliances with all its vassal states.

307
00:27:50,030 --> 00:27:51,600
I think the same, Your Majesty.

308
00:27:54,263 --> 00:27:57,720
Waging war brings no benefit to anyone.

309
00:27:58,960 --> 00:28:00,320
If we had not waged war,

310
00:28:02,683 --> 00:28:05,360
I could never have unified this Pagan Empire.

311
00:28:08,503 --> 00:28:09,920
However, a true leader

312
00:28:11,680 --> 00:28:13,920
must know when to wage war

313
00:28:15,257 --> 00:28:16,360
and when to cease.

314
00:28:21,280 --> 00:28:22,281
It is a pity.

315
00:28:27,443 --> 00:28:29,480
My father never once considers stopping.

316
00:28:34,443 --> 00:28:35,481
Your Father

317
00:28:36,952 --> 00:28:38,800
is a most valiant warrior.

318
00:28:41,880 --> 00:28:44,360
But if one hopes for this empire to live in peace and prosperity,

319
00:28:47,040 --> 00:28:48,520
Then the throne of Hongsawadi

320
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:51,440
cannot be entrusted to him.

321
00:28:53,710 --> 00:28:54,480
Grandfather.

322
00:28:56,320 --> 00:28:57,321
Mingyi Swa.

323
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:01,400
I shall have you succeed the Throne.

324
00:29:03,160 --> 00:29:05,921
And become the next King of Hongsawadi.

325
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:18,361
But Father is the Crown Prince.

326
00:29:19,480 --> 00:29:23,120
In the days to come, he must become the King of Hongsawadi.

327
00:29:25,223 --> 00:29:27,080
How can you change the succession?

328
00:29:27,560 --> 00:29:29,383
All things can change.

329
00:29:31,197 --> 00:29:32,920
I myself did not wish for it to be so.

330
00:29:33,880 --> 00:29:35,400
But as rulers of the land,

331
00:29:36,841 --> 00:29:38,910
the affairs of the state must come first.

332
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:43,040
We cannot afford to save face for anyone.

333
00:29:49,623 --> 00:29:50,924
After I pass away,

334
00:29:52,600 --> 00:29:54,760
the vassal states will surely contemplate rebellion.

335
00:29:56,283 --> 00:29:58,480
Regardless of who becomes the King of Hongsawadi,

336
00:29:59,160 --> 00:30:00,561
the kingdom shall fall into turmoil.

337
00:30:01,370 --> 00:30:03,520
If I appoint you this very day,

338
00:30:04,120 --> 00:30:05,440
while my prestige still remains,

339
00:30:06,560 --> 00:30:08,960
No one shall dare to incite treason,

340
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:12,320
not even your father.

341
00:30:15,057 --> 00:30:16,680
There is only Nares,

342
00:30:18,263 --> 00:30:20,120
whom I do not trust.

343
00:30:33,677 --> 00:30:35,920
Khun Phranai, what urgent matter brings you here?

344
00:30:39,590 --> 00:30:41,760
There is an urgent message from Prince Mingyi Swa, Your Highness.

345
00:30:55,560 --> 00:30:57,240
So, you will ascend as the King of Hongsawadi?

346
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:02,080
Grandfather has such a wish.

347
00:31:03,880 --> 00:31:04,881
But he said that

348
00:31:05,743 --> 00:31:07,520
whether this matter succeeds or not,

349
00:31:08,480 --> 00:31:09,520
it all depends on you.

350
00:31:10,657 --> 00:31:11,760
Why does it depend on me?

351
00:31:14,430 --> 00:31:15,800
If I ascend to the throne,

352
00:31:17,280 --> 00:31:20,440
most of the lords in Pagan are my own relatives.

353
00:31:21,400 --> 00:31:22,401
Even if they are displeased,

354
00:31:23,190 --> 00:31:25,280
they still fear the prestige of King Bayinnaung.

355
00:31:28,760 --> 00:31:31,440
But Phitsanulok and Ayutthaya are not related by blood,

356
00:31:32,161 --> 00:31:34,000
and are, in fact, your enemies.

357
00:31:34,817 --> 00:31:36,840
They might seize this opportunity to revolt.

358
00:31:39,117 --> 00:31:42,760
Once other lords see Ayutthaya and Phitsanulok rebelling,

359
00:31:43,690 --> 00:31:44,880
surely they will not remain still.

360
00:31:47,057 --> 00:31:50,200
Hongsawadi would then face wars on all sides.

361
00:31:50,500 --> 00:31:53,560
If Phitsanulok and Ayutthaya remain loyal,

362
00:31:59,823 --> 00:32:02,640
there will be no foreign wars and, consequently, no internal ones.

363
00:32:03,320 --> 00:32:04,321
Is it not so?

364
00:32:07,080 --> 00:32:08,081
Brother.

365
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:13,160
Whether Hongsawadi shall remain in peace

366
00:32:14,201 --> 00:32:15,202
or be consumed by flames,

367
00:32:17,617 --> 00:32:18,880
now depends entirely on you.

368
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:41,800
And will you stage a rebellion?

369
00:32:47,610 --> 00:32:50,280
The change of power in Hongsawadi is indeed a fitting opportunity, as you say.

370
00:32:52,357 --> 00:32:54,160
But I do not wish to fight Mingyi Swa.

371
00:32:54,883 --> 00:32:57,560
I fight only to liberate myself and be free.

372
00:32:59,611 --> 00:33:00,830
But if I do not fight

373
00:33:02,110 --> 00:33:04,200
and continue to submit to Mingyi Swa,

374
00:33:07,760 --> 00:33:09,401
then when shall I ever be free?

375
00:33:15,640 --> 00:33:16,760
An elephant that is tied up,

376
00:33:17,417 --> 00:33:20,480
whenever we undo its chains, it becomes free at that very moment.

377
00:33:24,720 --> 00:33:27,280
This depends entirely on the owner of the chains,

378
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:30,920
not on the elephant, is that not so, Your Highness?

379
00:33:58,556 --> 00:33:59,640
I desire

380
00:34:00,760 --> 00:34:02,120
to be my own master

381
00:34:02,920 --> 00:34:04,520
and be under no one's command.

382
00:34:09,190 --> 00:34:10,700
If I ascend the throne,

383
00:34:11,960 --> 00:34:15,800
will you rebel and refuse to be subject to Hongsawadi?

384
00:34:16,700 --> 00:34:20,080
Brother, that power is in your hands.

385
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:24,600
If only you would let go, I would be free.

386
00:34:28,937 --> 00:34:31,680
No one would have to perish at each other's hands.

387
00:34:35,040 --> 00:34:36,200
If you were to be free,

388
00:34:37,830 --> 00:34:39,040
what then would follow?

389
00:34:40,943 --> 00:34:42,440
I would then remain by your side.

390
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:48,361
Phitsanulok shall stand with Hongsawadi as an ally.

391
00:34:49,560 --> 00:34:51,920
In times of war, we shall fight together.

392
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:56,360
In times of peace, we shall live as brotherly kingdoms.

393
00:35:03,640 --> 00:35:05,760
I shall hasten to inform Grandfather this very moment.

394
00:35:46,663 --> 00:35:50,280
Your Highness, a message from the royal tutor Mangjaparo.

395
00:36:18,560 --> 00:36:19,561
Father!

396
00:36:28,160 --> 00:36:29,361
All of you, leave us.

397
00:36:41,640 --> 00:36:43,000
What wrong have I done?

398
00:36:46,437 --> 00:36:47,438
Jaisingh.

399
00:36:48,150 --> 00:36:51,080
- Listen to me, my son...
- I have trained in the arts of war for as long as I can remember.

400
00:36:52,480 --> 00:36:54,160
At the age of 13,

401
00:36:55,183 --> 00:36:57,680
I went to war and fought alongside you

402
00:36:58,110 --> 00:36:59,560
and King Tabinshwehti.

403
00:37:00,163 --> 00:37:01,600
I defeated the enemies

404
00:37:01,703 --> 00:37:03,960
until I was bestowed the name Jaisingh

405
00:37:04,640 --> 00:37:06,520
and appointed as the Crown Prince.

406
00:37:13,480 --> 00:37:14,950
The great Hongsawadi

407
00:37:15,662 --> 00:37:17,440
was built from my blood

408
00:37:18,163 --> 00:37:19,700
and the wounds on my body!

409
00:37:21,360 --> 00:37:23,320
Why have you done this to me, Father?

410
00:37:32,430 --> 00:37:34,300
How could you do this to me?

411
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:42,001
I

412
00:37:44,397 --> 00:37:46,240
and all the people of Hongsawadi

413
00:37:47,560 --> 00:37:50,000
are forever grateful for your service.

414
00:37:52,237 --> 00:37:53,560
But, my son,

415
00:37:55,683 --> 00:37:58,481
you are capable of building an empire,

416
00:38:00,560 --> 00:38:03,480
but you may not be able to keep it.

417
00:38:03,840 --> 00:38:07,040
I maintain it still, with my own sword!

418
00:38:07,817 --> 00:38:11,640
You will lead the kingdom into a war

419
00:38:13,117 --> 00:38:14,770
that shall never end.

420
00:38:15,040 --> 00:38:18,800
I shall win every war. Why then should I fear?

421
00:38:20,763 --> 00:38:22,240
True that I love my son,

422
00:38:23,803 --> 00:38:25,804
but I have bathed in blood,

423
00:38:26,030 --> 00:38:28,400
to build such a great Pagan Empire.

424
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:31,560
You cannot give it to another. I will not allow it!

425
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:54,360
Make haste to the audience, Your Highness.

426
00:38:55,143 --> 00:38:57,120
His Majesty has commanded that

427
00:38:57,663 --> 00:38:59,720
whenever you arrive,

428
00:39:00,680 --> 00:39:02,720
you are to be brought before him at once,

429
00:39:03,080 --> 00:39:04,121
without delay.

430
00:39:18,197 --> 00:39:19,198
Grandfather.

431
00:39:52,477 --> 00:39:53,640
Mingyi Swa.

432
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:57,480
Pay respects to Grandfather.

433
00:40:41,383 --> 00:40:42,384
Grandfather.

434
00:41:03,310 --> 00:41:06,400
Mingyi Swa returned to Hongsawadi

435
00:41:06,910 --> 00:41:08,640
with a grand dream.

436
00:41:12,357 --> 00:41:15,440
Peace between the two lands

437
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:17,640
is now within reach.

438
00:41:20,410 --> 00:41:23,921
The destiny between Mingyi Swa and I

439
00:41:24,680 --> 00:41:26,240
was not ordained to be so.

440
00:41:29,423 --> 00:41:32,000
King Bayinnaung of Hongsawadi passed away

441
00:41:32,840 --> 00:41:35,160
before he could appoint Mingyi Swa

442
00:41:36,243 --> 00:41:38,320
as the new king of Hongsawadi.

443
00:41:46,480 --> 00:41:50,240
The dream that Ayutthaya and Hongsawadi

444
00:41:51,240 --> 00:41:53,241
would be brotherly kingdoms

445
00:41:55,200 --> 00:41:57,201
thus perished along with him.

446
00:42:19,077 --> 00:42:22,600
Once the ritual of the water of allegiance has been performed,

447
00:42:22,880 --> 00:42:25,601
should anyone harbor thoughts of betrayal against me,

448
00:42:26,000 --> 00:42:27,320
may they suffer a miserable death.

449
00:42:27,701 --> 00:42:29,280
Take great care of yourself.

450
00:42:29,600 --> 00:42:33,200
From this moment on, the fires of war shall spread everywhere.

451
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:41,161
If we cannot control Inwa, I shall never know a peaceful sleep.

452
00:42:41,477 --> 00:42:43,520
You must go and ask for forgiveness from the King of Inwa

453
00:42:43,630 --> 00:42:46,040
and enter into the marriage ceremony with Natshin Medaw.

454
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:47,840
If you can endure it no longer, then come with me.

455
00:42:48,163 --> 00:42:50,480
Within the walls of Phitsanulok, I am the sovereign.

456
00:42:51,120 --> 00:42:52,840
I shall not allow anyone to harm you, Brother.

457
00:42:53,197 --> 00:42:55,520
Whatever is rightfully mine,

458
00:42:56,120 --> 00:42:57,920
I must possess it.
